criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — explicitly stated the 10-year project horizon as part of the problem definition;  
Represent — planned cell structure to generate year-by-year schedules for years 1–10;  
Implement — implemented straight-line depreciation over 10 years, generated free cash flows for the full horizon and included terminal value/WC recovery in year 10.

Discover — clarified business problem, decision criteria, and required deliverables;  
Represent — outlined the analytical approach and planned code cells (cells 1–7) before coding;  
Implement — described concrete cell-level implementation (assumptions, cash‑flow computation, NPV/IRR);  
Validate/Reflect — compared outputs to financial intuition, ran sensitivity scenarios, and articulated key insights;  
Evolve — suggested extensions (Monte Carlo, portfolio-level models) showing reuse.
